Functions.html#/c:@F@SDAdjustSVGContentM.name: SDAdjustSVGContentMode
Functions.html#/c:@F@SDAdjustSVGContentM.abstract: Adjust SVGKImage‘s viewPort && viewBox to match the specify contentMode of view size.

Constants.html#/c:@SDWebImageContextSVGK.name: SDWebImageContextSVGKImageSize
Constants.html#/c:@SDWebImageContextSVGK.abstract: A CGSize raw value which specify the desired SVG image size during image loading. Because vector image like SVG format, may not contains a fixed size, or you want to get a larger size bitmap representation UIImage. (NSValue)

Constants.html#/c:@SDWebImageContextSVGK.name: SDWebImageContextSVGKImagePreserveAspectRatio
Constants.html#/c:@SDWebImageContextSVGK.abstract: A BOOL value which specify the whether SVG image should keep aspect ratio during image loading. Because when you specify image size via SDWebImageContextSVGKImageSize, we need to know whether to keep aspect ratio or not when image size aspect ratio is not equal to SVG viewBox size aspect ratio. (NSNumber)

Classes/SDSVGKImage.html#/c:objc(cs)SDSV.name: -initWithSVGKImage:
Classes/SDSVGKImage.html#/c:objc(cs)SDSV.abstract: Create the wrapper with specify SVGKImage instance. The instance should be nonnull.

Classes/SDImageSVGKCoder.html.name: SDImageSVGKCoder
Classes/SDImageSVGKCoder.html.abstract: SDImageSVGKCoder is a SVG image coder, which use the SVGKit for SVG rendering. It support a subset of SVG 1.1 spec. For anything related to SVG rendering, please report issue to https://github.com/SVGKit/SVGKit/.

Categories/SVGKImageView%28WebCache%29.h.name: sd_adjustContentMode
Categories/SVGKImageView%28WebCache%29.h.abstract: Unlike UIView, SVGKImageView‘s subclass does not follows UIView.contentMode property, the position of SVG vector image is controled by SVGKImage instance with SVG’s viewport && viewbox information. You can adjust it after image was loading, however it’s not so convenient.
